H0.text: where does the cell spend most of its time in the cell cycle. Prophase

H1.text: where does the cell spend most of its time in the cell cycle. Metaphase

H2.text: where does the cell spend most of its time in the cell cycle. Anaphase

H3.text: where does the cell spend most of its time in the cell cycle. Interphase

A4.text: Interphase is the phase of the cell cycle in which a typical cell spends 90% of its life.

A5.text: Most cells of adult mammals spend about 24 hours in interphase; this accounts for about 90%-96% of the total time involved in cell division.
